<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149259" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2">Changes the stacking order of a selected object.</paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3154703" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="E" localize="false"><link href="text/shared/00/00040501.xhp#anordnung"><embedvar href="text/shared/00/00000004.xhp#wie"/></link></paragraph>
<embed href="text/simpress/guide/select_object.xhp#select_object"/>
<paragraph role="note" id="par_id3154370" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="3">Each object you place in your document is successively stacked on the preceding object. Objects on the control layer are always at the top of the stacking order. </paragraph>
<paragraph role="note" id="par_id3154488" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="4">To select an object that is covered by another object, hold down <switchinline select="sys"><caseinline select="MAC">Option 
</caseinline><defaultinline>Alt</defaultinline></switchinline>.</paragraph>
